"...Thank you for your hard work. Was the research budget sufficient?" [r]
Ishii-san said as he put the printed report back into the case. [l][r]
"It was too much. Please give me some time to return it to your account."[l][r]
Without replying to my words, Ishii-san looked towards the far northwestern sky. [l][r]
[r] Her shoulders were shaking. I wondered if she was crying, but I was wrong. [l] A faint chuckle was coming from her mouth. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"...Can you laugh?" [l][r]
"It's hilarious." [l][r]

[r] Ishii-san chuckled and replied: [r]
With the same smile, she took a deep breath and wiped the corners of her eyes. [l][r]
Then, as if pondering for a moment, he put his hand to his chin and suddenly spoke again. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"...Well, for example, what were you thinking when you died in that world?" [l][r]

"Eh? ... [l] Yes, I was thinking, 'Now I can finally die' ... or something like that." [l][r]

"Right? But those children were different. They lived until the very last moment, and must have slept happily imagining what they would do next. [l]... Even if the result was a sad separation." [l][r]

[r] Ishii-san continued, searching for words, as if he was pondering alone, without even glancing at me. [l][r]

"Those children must have remembered those feelings once again. ... I'm sure. At least, that's what I think." [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"...What should we do now?" [l][r]
Being unsophisticated, I can only speak in such formal terms. [l]But Ishii-san doesn't seem dissatisfied. He looks up at the sky and squints his eyes happily. [l][r]

[r] "You mean me? I do it as usual. I work, I eat, I sleep. That's it. [l][r]
…But please don’t get me wrong. I will not give up on these women, who are both my respected friends and my beloved family. [l][r]
Work, gain strength, and take off. Beyond the journey of those children. [l][r]
On my plane..." [l][r]
[r]While rotating your body lightly,
"Well," said Ishii-san, laughing. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"I'm jealous," I say, without any pretense. [l][r]

"Do you want to ride too?" Ishii-san asked, looking at me for the first time. [l][r]
I immediately replied, "With pleasure." [l][r]

[r]"Just kidding. Take care of your family."[l][r]
"Yes, I do. They are also my precious family." [l][r]
"Okay. I'll tell your wife." [l][r]
"Please." [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
[r]When I answered, Ishii-san smiled mischievously, just like Yuri, then looked up at the sky again with his straight eyes, just like Chito. [l][r]

I will follow that example. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

